text_blocks.content: 1 Instruction No. 22: Count Four: Transportation of a Minor to Engage in Illegal Sexual Activity - Third Element

The third element of Count Four which the Government must prove beyond a reasonable doubt is that Ms. Maxwell knew that Jane was less than seventeen years old at the time of the acts alleged in Count Four of the Indictment.
